slurm-exporter (1.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial Debian package release
  * Comprehensive SLURM metrics collection covering jobs, nodes, partitions, 
    accounts, fairshare policies, and QoS settings
  * Advanced job analytics engine with efficiency monitoring, waste detection, 
    and bottleneck analysis
  * High performance with intelligent caching, connection pooling, and batch 
    processing
  * Production-ready security hardening with TLS, authentication, and audit 
    compliance
  * Native Kubernetes and container support with Helm charts and Docker images
  * Real-time monitoring with pre-built Grafana dashboards and Prometheus 
    alerting rules
  * Comprehensive documentation and deployment guides
  * Multi-architecture support (amd64, arm64, armhf, armel, i386)

 -- SLURM Exporter Team <maintainers@slurm-exporter.io>  Mon, 15 Jan 2024 10:00:00 +0000

